Read on about Charis

Charis Abrams

Principal / CEO / Founder

In the financial crash Charis closed her Utah operation and moved to Las Vegas. Seeing opportunity in REO, Charis quickly got her real estate brokers license and became the managing broker of one of the valley's largest independent brokerages.

During this time, Charis personally sold over 3,000 SFR for her banking clients and traded over $900,000,000 NPL trades making her one of the top producing female reale state agents in the country.

Charis differs from a traditional mortgage broker or real estate agent in many respects. Between 2010- 2014, Charis was the architect and President of a real estate software platform. That platform was the first to take a defaulting note from first pay default all the way through REO disposition and much more.

In 2012, she created a module that allowed her company to be the first software to analyze SFR in mass nationwide. This allowed groups such as Progress Residential to have actionable data on over $16,000,000,000 in SFR assets across 17 markets in 6 months.

The software business gave her the unique experience of sitting at the intersection of Bank/ Investor, Servicer, Acquisition Fund, Escrow/ Title company and Broker. "I wasn't there for just one sale; I was there to listen to each stake holder and implement their needs into our software." This gave her a deep understanding of each of their processes and how to maneuver between them.

This in-depth knowledge of not only mortgage, but all of the supporting industries is what led her to the NON-QM mortgage space and to build a company not just for now but for the future.

Jason A.

Chief revenue Officer

Jason serves as the Chief Revenue Officer at Max Capital Lending, a nationwide private lending firm specializing in innovative financing solutions for real estate investors. With over 23 years of experience and more than 7,500 successful transactions, Jason brings a wealth of industry knowledge, strategic insight, and a relentless drive for results.

Recognized as one of the Nation's’ top-selling agents, Jason earned the #1 ranking for Luxury Homes of Las Vegas for ten consecutive years (2006–2016) and held the #11 spot worldwide for Re/Max International in 2005. His career is defined by passion, precision, and a deep commitment to client success.

Jason’s transition into private lending is a natural evolution of his real estate journey. His ability to build influential relationships, understand market dynamics, and deliver tailored solutions makes him a powerful asset to Max Capital Lending’s leadership team. As CRO, he leads with creativity and vision—driving revenue growth, expanding strategic partnerships, and ensuring the company continues to meet the evolving needs of investors nationwide.

Beyond his professional achievements, Jason is the founder of S4, a marketing firm focused on real estate education events, and a respected speaker at institutions like the Robert Allen Institute, Rich Dad Poor Dad Education, and Millionaire Academy.

Jason’s dedication to excellence, education, and innovation continues to shape the future of real estate finance. At Max Capital Lending, he is committed to empowering investors with the tools, funding, and guidance they need to succeed.

Carlo Lu

Account Representative

Carlo Lu embarked on a career journey that began in the dynamic realm of tech startups. In these early experiences, he honed his skills in innovation, adaptability, and the art of forging valuable connections. Inspired by a desire to contribute to societal well-being, Carlo later transitioned to working with non-profit organizations dedicated to raising awareness and support for teenage abuse issues. This unique combination of tech-driven acumen and a commitment to social causes has shaped Carlo’s perspective and approach to business.


As one of our Account Reps, Carlo brings this distinctive background to the forefront, driving our efforts to establish and support new business relationships. His youthful energy, coupled with a wealth of experience in diverse environments, sets him apart in navigating the evolving landscape of lending.


Passion for Positive Impact:

Beyond his professional endeavors, Carlo remains dedicated to making a positive impact. His past work in non-profit organizations underscores a commitment to social responsibility, aligning seamlessly with our values as a company.


Collaborative Approach:

Known for his collaborative spirit and innovative mindset, Carlo is a key player in fostering strong partnerships and understanding the unique needs of our borrowers. His ability to bridge the gap between technology, social awareness, and lending positions him as a catalyst for positive change within our organization.


We are thrilled to have Carlo on board, propelling our company's growth and commitment to responsible and impactful lending. His dynamic approach and passion for both business success and community well-being make him an invaluable asset to our team.
